{
 "cells": [
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b6f0aa85",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Conjunctions\n",
    "In this tutorial we consider the simulation we described in [quickstart](<./quickstart.ipynb>), but instead of stopping at a collision, to then have the possibility to react and proceed, we will only track conjunctions and switch off collisions.\n",
    "\n",
    "Let us start with some imports:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "c9b316b3-8d04-4b55-8395-54be3213bd03",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# core imports\n",
    "import cascade as csc\n",
    "import pykep as pk\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import heyoka as hy\n",
    "\n",
    "# plotting\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5e4c4616",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## The dynamics\n",
    "\n",
    "For this tutorial we will make use the same non dimensional Keplerian dynamics used in [quickstart](<./quickstart.ipynb>).\n",
    "\n",
    "Let us instantiate it:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "72c0addd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dyn = csc.dynamics.kepler(mu = 1)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "826204f1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## The initial conditions\n",
    "\n",
    "As initial conditions we also repeat the same as in [quickstart](<./quickstart.ipynb>).\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "1b25e27e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "N = 1000 # number of objects simulated\n",
    "# The following numpy array will hold all the initial conditions and object radius [x,y,z,vx,vy,vz,r]\n",
    "ic_state = np.zeros((N, 7))\n",
    "# We generate randomly orbital parameters and imensions and transform them to Cartesian state. Note we make use of nondimensional units as defined in the dynamics.\n",
    "for i in range(N):\n",
    "    a = np.random.uniform(1.02, 1.3)\n",
    "    e = np.random.uniform(0, 0.02)\n",
    "    inc = np.random.uniform(np.pi/3, np.pi/3 + 0.05)\n",
    "    om = np.random.uniform(0, 2*np.pi)\n",
    "    Om = np.random.uniform(np.pi/3, np.pi/3 + 0.05)\n",
    "    nu = np.random.uniform(0, 2*np.pi)\n",
    "    size = np.random.uniform(1e-3/2, 1e-4)\n",
    "    r, v = pk.par2ic([a, e, inc, Om, om, nu], mu = 1.)\n",
    "    ic_state[i][:3] = r\n",
    "    ic_state[i][3:6] = v\n",
    "    ic_state[i][6] = size"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "dd021413",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "... and we visualize them in proportion to a central body of radius 0.5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "3ca52664",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')\n",
    "\n",
    "r = 0.5\n",
    "u, v = np.mgrid[0:2*np.pi:20j, 0:np.pi:10j]\n",
    "x = r*np.cos(u)*np.sin(v)\n",
    "y = r*np.sin(u)*np.sin(v)\n",
    "z = r*np.cos(v)\n",
    "ax.plot_wireframe(x, y, z, color=\"r\", alpha=0.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.scatter3D(ic_state[:,0], ic_state[:,1], ic_state[:,2], alpha=0.2, s= 1, c='k')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(-1,1)\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(-1,1)\n",
    "ax.set_zlim(-1,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.view_init(45,15)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0afaaa10",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Building the simulation\n",
    "\n",
    "Since we want to track conjunctions and ignore possible collisions, we instantiate the simulation as :"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "56d0dad5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sim = csc.sim(state = ic_state, dyn=dyn, ct = 2*np.pi / 90, conj_thresh = 1e-2, min_coll_radius=float('inf'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "77eda31b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Two arguments have been added with respect to the similar simulation presented in [quickstart](<./quickstart.ipynb>). The argument ``conj_thresh`` defines the conjunction threshold. All conjunction events with closest distance smaller than ``conj_thresh`` will be detected and reported. The argument ``min_coll_radius`` ignores all collisions between objects having radius smaller than its value. In this case we use infinity hence switching off all collision events.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Running the simulation "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "1f8b7865",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# This will try to propagate all the orbits up to the final time is reached (roughly three orbits)\n",
    "oc = sim.propagate_until(6 * np.pi)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b9451662",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "At the end of this simulation all conjunctions will be stored in the attribute {class}`cascade.sim.conjunctions`. This contains in each line the idx of the two objects, the conjunction time, the closest distance and the states of the two particles at the conjunction."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "6cdf61ce",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Number of conjunctions:  473\n",
      "Minimal conjunction distance:  0.00044759696356493084\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "conj_n = len(sim.conjunctions)\n",
    "conj_d = sim.conjunctions['dist']\n",
    "print(\"Number of conjunctions: \", len(sim.conjunctions))\n",
    "print(\"Minimal conjunction distance: \", min(conj_d))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3cffab7d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Plotting the conjunction positions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "7426e1e3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')\n",
    "\n",
    "r = 0.5\n",
    "u, v = np.mgrid[0:2*np.pi:20j, 0:np.pi:10j]\n",
    "x = r*np.cos(u)*np.sin(v)\n",
    "y = r*np.sin(u)*np.sin(v)\n",
    "z = r*np.cos(v)\n",
    "ax.plot_wireframe(x, y, z, color=\"r\", alpha=0.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.scatter3D(ic_state[:,0], ic_state[:,1], ic_state[:,2], alpha=0.2, s= 1, c='k')\n",
    "\n",
    "pos = np.array([sim.conjunctions[i][4][:3] for i in range(conj_n)])\n",
    "ax.scatter3D(pos[:,0], pos[:,1], pos[:,2], alpha=1, s= 3, c='r')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(-1,1)\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(-1,1)\n",
    "ax.set_zlim(-1,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.view_init(45,15)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8ad925b1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "as expected, in this case, conjunctions happen more or less uniformly in the Keplerian ring defined by the orbits."
   ]
  }
 ],
